==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Helleborein
<hw>Hel`le*bo"re*in</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A poisonous glucoside accompanying helleborin in several species of
hellebore, and extracted as a white crystalline substance with a
bittersweet taste. It has a strong action on the heart, resembling
digitalin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Helleborin</ent>⟦br⟧
